Class StartEpoch<NodeIDType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umass.cs.protocoltask.json.ProtocolPacket<NodeIDType,ReconfigurationPacket.PacketType>
      • edu.umass.cs.reconfiguration.reconfigurationpackets.ReconfigurationPacket<NodeIDType>
        • edu.umass.cs.reconfiguration.reconfigurationpackets.BasicReconfigurationPacket<NodeIDType>
          • edu.umass.cs.reconfiguration.reconfigurationpackets.StartEpoch<NodeIDType>
  • Type Parameters:
    NodeIDType - FIXME: This class is increasingly under risk of becoming the kitchen sink for every piece of information needed anywhere in the reconfiguration protocol sequence. A better design may be to carry the causal reconfiguration packet (create, delete, reconfigureRC, etc.) here instead of carrying all fields in all startEpoch packets.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Request, Byteable, ProtocolEvent<ReconfigurationPacket.PacketType,java.lang.String>, ThresholdProtocolEvent<NodeIDType,ReconfigurationPacket.PacketType,java.lang.String>, Keyable<java.lang.String>, Summarizable
